    <h1><b>Jalandhar</b></h1>
    <hr />
    <p>Jalandhar is the north-western city in Punjab. The oldest city of Punjab has seen very fast development and urbanization and has become a high industrial centre. The city was earlier known as Prasthala during the period of Mahabharata. And During the British era, it was known as Jullundur.</p>
    <br />
    <h1><b>Attractions</b></h1>
    <hr />
    <h3><b>Devi Talab Mandir</b></h3>
    <p>
    This is situated in the heart of the city and has been recently renovated. Apart from this, there is also another temple of Kali close to Devi Talab Mandir.
    </p>
    <h3><b>Tulsi Mandir</b></h3>
    <p>There is a tank on one side of the temple and was said to be the bathing place of the demon Jalandhara.</p>
    <br />
    <h1><b>What to Buy</b></h1>
    <hr />
    <p>
    Jalandhar is very famous for the handicrafts and handlooms and it is better to go for old and city markets rather than those malls for all these things.
    </p>
<br />
<h1><b>What to Eat and Drink</b></h1>
<hr />
<p>
The cuisines are very simple and cooked with much love. The food is mostly prepared in desi ghee and the sweets like ladoos and pinnis are very famous. One should eat the local flavor and go for stuffed parathas, halwas, sarson ka saag, etc.
</p>
